cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the design and evaluation of a competition focused on reactive synthesis, which is a topic closely related to logic and automata theory. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as reactive synthesis involves the automatic generation of programs from specifications, which is a core problem in programming languages research. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as reactive synthesis has applications in software engineering, particularly in the development of correct-by-construction systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as reactive synthesis can be seen as a problem in AI, specifically in the area of automated planning and decision making. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as reactive synthesis involves the synthesis of automata from specifications, which is a topic within formal languages and automata theory.
